!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

excited /ɪkˈsaɪtɪd/

1. ADJ If you are excited , you are so happy that you cannot relax, especially because you are thinking about something pleasant that is going to happen to you. 兴奋的 

例： I was excited about the possibility of playing football again. 想到有可能再次踢足球，我很兴奋。 

2. excitedly ADV 兴奋地 [ADV with v] 

例： 'You're coming?' he said excitedly. 'That's fantastic! That's incredible!' “你要来？”他兴奋地说，“太棒了！简直难以置信！” 

3. ADJ If you are excited , you are worried or angry about something, and so you are very alert and cannot relax. 焦躁不安的; 激愤的 

例： I don't think there's any reason to get excited about inflation. 我认为没理由因通货膨胀而焦虑。 

4. excitedly ADV 焦躁不安地; 激愤地 [ADV with v] 

例： Larry rose excitedly to the edge of his seat, shook a fist at us and spat. 拉里激愤地从座位上站了起来，向我们又晃拳头又啐唾沫。

</div>

